{
  "texts": [
    "Recently, CNNs have replaced traditional feature engineering techniques in various computer vision applications.",
    "The notable difference is that the image features are learnt from the data instead of manually designing them.",
    "CNN (LeCun et al. 2015) is a type of neural network model for image processing inspired by the animal visual cortex.",
    "The key component of CNNs are the convolutional layers that consist of neurons each processing data only for their receptive field.",
    "Due to the shared-weight architecture, these neurons fundamentally perform the convolution operation to the input with a filter defined by the weights of the neurons."
  ]
}